The instruction asks to extract the numeric value from the text in column B and determine the correct decimal sign (comma → dot). A robust Excel formula that works for the shown formats is:

```
=VALUE(
    SUBSTITUTE(
        SUBSTITUTE(
            SUBSTITUTE(
                SUBSTITUTE(
                    TRIM(B2), "USD", "")
                , "EUR", "")
            , " ", "")
        , ",", ".")
